						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is mutilated and incomplete. It seems to record a gift of land after purchase for 3 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold from the temple itself of Tirumāgāḷattu-Mahādēva at Ambar in Ambar-nāḍu for burning a perpetual lamp before the god, by a person named <hi rend="bold">Vāṇarāyaṉ Araṅgaṉ Mādēvaṉ.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
